{"type":"text","timestamp":1782714401837,"sessionID":"ses_0edf92fdcffeIVMHfhZkGdAVyf","part":{"id":"prt_f120edbec001PEDZqA3n70Fs8Q","messageID":"msg_f120eab0e001b72sPeD90N6tIs","sessionID":"ses_0edf92fdcffeIVMHfhZkGdAVyf","type":"text","text":"Aligned the phase-06/profile repair cluster with the Android source and refreshed its authority evidence.\n\nChanged files:\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj`: removed invented toast behavior for profile edit and section taps; those handlers are now inert like the source screen, while logout flow stays intact.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile/profile_route_service.cj`: removed placeholder-message helpers; kept only real route/back/logout transition behavior.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile/profile_store.cj`: removed fake profile action-feedback surfaces; kept static identity, section count, logout, and logout route.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase06_profile_capabilities_verification_test.cj`: updated phase-06 tests to assert the real translated profile scope: static identity, back behavior, logout transition, and startup resolution.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`: updated 7 touched rows so profile rows no longer claim explicit placeholder-action messaging and source-test replacement rows point at current focused tests.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`: synced markdown mirror via the authority patch tool.\n\nCommands run:\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\.cangjie-sdk\\6.1\\cangjie\\build-tools\\tools\\bin\\cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` from `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie` with the final-coverage env overlay\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\opencode\\profile-matrix-patch.json --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n\nBuild result:\n- PASS: bounded phase-06/final-coverage test reproduction succeeded with `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos`\n- Existing warnings only; no new blocker introduced\n\nPlan changes:\n- none\n\nDeferred issues:\n- none added for this cluster\n- Remaining whole-project medium findings are outside this cluster: broad shell/endpoint concentration and the separate `Coming soon!` login placeholders that appear source-backed rather than invented by this repair\n\nHigh-risk gaps fixed:\n- Removed invented target behavior in profile: source `Profile.kt` has empty edit/card click handlers, so the target no longer shows toast feedback there.\n- Tightened profile authority evidence to precise profile route/store/page endpoints instead of removed placeholder-message helpers.\n- Updated source-test replacement rows so they reference the current focused target tests and current accepted test gate.\n\nRemaining deferred gaps:\n- No new deferred feature or capability gaps in the scoped cluster.\n- Whole-project LoC and target-structure warnings still need their own sweep if you want to continue beyond this cluster.\n\nTests added or updated:\n- Updated `phase06_profile_capabilities_verification_test.cj` to keep:\n  - `profileStorePreservesStaticIdentity`\n  - `profileStorePreservesLogoutRoute`\n  - `profileStorePreservesBackAndLogoutRoutes`\n  - `profileLogoutTransitionResetsRouteStateAndReturnsOnboarding`\n  - `profileBackRouteUsesTheNavigationStackWhenPresent`\n  - `startupResolverReturnsOnboardingAfterLogoutStyleState`\n  - `sourceExampleUnitAssertionIntentIsCoveredByTargetHarness`\n\nAnother final coverage pass recommended:\n- Yes, but only for the remaining whole-project structure clusters and any stale report rows that still mention old phase-06 test names.\n- Not needed for this profile implement-or-structure cluster itself unless you want the workflow reports regenerated to clear stale generated summaries.","time":{"start":1782714391532,"end":1782714401834}}}
